Field Notes: This area is very overgrown with salmon berry

The forest at this site is the result of neglected and unmanaged natural regrowth from logging, probably sometime in the 1940s or 1950s. Red Alder, Douglas fir and non-native invasive plants are dominant. Doug Fir and Red Cedar are slowly taking over.
Trees are all about 20-30 years old
pretty nice area, not a lot of damage from farming or invasive species
